The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of automated facial landmark detection, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of salient patches and feature extraction is a common technique in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed system in low-resolution images, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
